title: Appointments to Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong
content_text:
p>
    The Government announced today (September 14) the appointment of three new 
    members and the re-appointment of six incumbent members to the Veterinary 
    Surgeons Board of Hong Kong for three years from September 15, 2012, to 
    September 14, 2015. The three new members are Dr Diane Lu Dah-an, Dr Tint Naing and Dr Ian James 
    Urquhart. Dr Diane Lu has been registered with the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong 
    Kong since 1999. She is currently a small-animal veterinary practitioner

Kong since 1999. She is currently a small-animal veterinary practitioner 
    specialising in neurology. Dr Tint Naing has been registered with the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong 
    Kong since 1998. He is currently the practice owner and principal veterinary 
    surgeon of a veterinary clinic. He is also a Diplomate of the American Board 
    of Veterinary Practitioners in Canine and Feline Practice. Dr Ian James Urquhart has been registered with the Veterinary Surgeons Board

of Hong Kong since 1999. Dr Urquhart is currently a partner of a veterinary 
    clinic and member of the subcommittee of the Hong Kong Veterinary 
    Association, the largest veterinary organisation in Hong Kong. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed the new members 
    and those re-appointed to the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong. He 
    looked forward to their contribution in upholding veterinary standards to 
    meet the increasing demand for quality veterinary services. Dr Ko also thanked the retiring members - Dr Katriona Christine Ferguson

Bradley, Dr Lawrence Chan Wai-him and Dr Kenneth Lam Ka-ho - for their 
    dedication and valuable advice to the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong 
    during their term of appointment. Enacted in 1997, the Veterinary Surgeons Registration Ordinance (Cap 529) 
    provides for the establishment of the Veterinary Surgeons Board, which is 
    responsible for the regulation of the practice of veterinary surgery, the 
    registration of veterinary surgeons, and the disciplinary control of the

registration of veterinary surgeons, and the disciplinary control of the professional activities of registered veterinary surgeons in Hong Kong. Following is the membership list of the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong as from September 15: Chairman
